1.title: Dude, Where's My School?
1.plot: The Quads win the family an all-expenses paid vacation to Hollywood, but soon find themselves caught up in a case of mistaken identity, which leads to an outrageous adventure that turns out to be the best vacation ever.

2.title: Wrestle-Mae-nia
2.plot: A misunderstanding almost causes the quads to break up Mae and Miles and disrupt the boys' plans to attend a wrestling match.

3.title: Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & BeyDawncé
3.plot: Nicky, Ricky and Dicky accidentally turn Dawn into "BeyDawnce" using techniques they've learned in their human behavior class to help her overcome her fear of auditioning for the Glee Club.

4.title: It's a Hard Knocks Life
4.plot: Dawn joins a ballet class excited to have her own activity away from her brothers, only to have her plan spoiled when the boys join the class too. Guest Star: Maddie Ziegler

5.title: Sympathy for the Squishy
5.plot: Nicky, Dicky, and Dawn challenge Ricky's firm disbelief in superstitions, but when they go too far in proving him wrong, they call on Science Bob to bring Ricky back to reality. Guest Star: Science Bob

6.title: The Harper Quad-Jobbers
6.plot: The quads try to earn money for a pool so that their house can be the place everyone wants to hang out at during the summer.

7.title: Leader of the Stack
7.plot: It's Quad vs. Quad in the election for class president. Ricky thinks he has the race locked up, but is surprised when Dawn enters. Things get even messier when Nicky and Dicky go from their running mates to their rivals.

8.title: Quadentity Crisis
8.plot: When the quads each try to be someone they are not, they all learn a valuable lesson about being true to themselves.

9.title: Quadbusters
9.plot: When the quads are pressured by older kids to sneak out after curfew and hang out at Get Sporty, they discover that the store is haunted.

10.title: Quadcodile Dundee
10.plot: The quads are taught a lesson by Tom and Anne when they are forced to wait in line like everyone else when Isaiah Thomas comes to the store to sign his new shoes.

11.title: House Crushing for Dummies
11.plot: The quads worry that Britt has developed a "house crush" on Dawn, and have to figure out a way to get him to stop liking her before his secret is discovered and he is sent back to Australia.

12.title: We'll Always Have Parasites
12.plot: Dawn and Mae get jobs to help pay for a trip to Paris, but their plans get complicated when the boys discover that they can use complaining at restaurants to their benefit.

13.title: Quadspiracy Theory
13.plot: When Nicky, Ricky, and Dawn discover that Britt has been hanging out with their friends without them, they start to question his motives.

14.title: Lasties with Firsties
14.plot: After Mae gets accepted to a new boarding school, Dawn is desperate to make lasting memories with her best friend before she leaves; Nicky and Ricky secretly audition new best friends for Dawn.

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Nicky, Ricky, Dicky and Dawn are quadruplets with only two things in common: their birthday and parents. This dynamic foursome battle sibling rivalry at every turn, but in the end when they are together, nothing can stop them.

2.title: Dawn Moves Out
2.plot: Dawn grows tired of her brothers' antics and moves into her own room; the quads realize that they need each other more than they think.

3.title: Get Sporty-er!
3.plot: Dawn is suspicious when the boys are smitten by a new girl at school; Tom's former ice dancing rival plans to open his own sporting goods store.

4.title: Field of Brains
4.plot: The quads try to impress Josie by watching a horror movie, but they quickly regret their decision when they start to believe their parents are zombies.

5.title: Scaredy Dance
5.plot: The quads excitement for the Halloween school dance is outdone only by their parents who are chaperoning.

6.title: Remote Control Control
6.plot: Dicky and Dawn's constant battle for control of the remote nearly ruins Tom and Anne's anniversary.

7.title: PooDunnit
7.plot: Nicky, Ricky, Dicky and Dawn's parents figure out who didn't flush the toilet.

8.title: I Got Your Back
8.plot: Dawn makes the soccer team, but learns that the others make jokes at Nicky's expense.

9.title: The Sad Tail of Gary-Chip-Tiny-Elvis-Squishy-Paws
9.plot: When the dog stops a theft at Get Sporty, the quads argue publicly about his name.

10.title: Santa's Little Harpers
10.plot: While trying to earn money for the newest video game console, the quads compete for tips.

11.title: The Quadfather
11.plot: The quads decide that they want to be more grown up and have individual parties for their 10th birthday.

12.title: The Quad-Test
12.plot: The quads compete among themselves for a month with no chores. One of them goes so far as to recruit Science Bob for extra help in winning the contest.

13.title: The Secret
13.plot: When Dawn finds out the boys have been keeping things from her, she decides that they all must share a secret to repair the circle of trust. Meanwhile, Tom and Anne plan a fashion show.

14.title: Take the Money and Run
14.plot: Dawn sells a special bracelet that her mother gave her in order to make some money; the boys try to outsmart Tom when he takes away their video games.

15.title: Valentime's Day
15.plot: The Quads get assigned a project to do something special for someone else on Valentine's Day, but not everything goes according to plan and they start to think they are cursed.

16.title: Piggy, Piggy, Piggy & Dawn
16.plot: Dawn wants to change the quads' puppet routine for the talent show, but she grows frustrated after always being outvoted by her brothers.

17.title: Quad-ventures in Babysitting
17.plot: The quads beg their parents to allow Josie to be their new babysitter.

18.title: M.D. Day
18.plot: The Quads fear the doctor, but they are determined to make it thru this year's routine exams to get the cookie tower that has eluded them for so long.

19.title: Abraquadabra
19.plot: When Ricky gets punished for using smoke pellets in the house, his siblings decide to sneak him out to a party so he can see one of his idols perform.

20.title: Family Matters
20.plot: The quads attempt to get out of family night by introducing Tom and Anne to another couple so they can become friends.

1.title: Wanted: The Sugar Beet Gang
1.plot: The quads argue about how to complete their history assignment.

2.title: No Ifs, Ands, or But-ers
2.plot: The quads turn their garage into an awesome hangout space, improving their social status.

3.title: Urban Legend Outfitters
3.plot: When Dawn fakes a story for her column, the urban legend of Pigfoot begins to take over Edgewood.

4.title: Do-It-All Dawn
4.plot: Dawn assures her parents that she can handle it all when she begins to play tuba.

5.title: Unhappy Campers
5.plot: When the quads go to summer camp, they realize they can establish new identities. This puts Dawn in an uncomfortable position when she refers to Dicky as her "boyfriend" in order to try and impress her new friends.

6.title: Mall in the Family
6.plot: The quads convince their parents that they are responsible enough to explore the mall on their own.

7.title: I Want Candace
7.plot: Nicky, Ricky and Dicky ruin Dawn's chance to meet her idol, and must find a way to make it up to her.

8.title: Sweet Foot Rides
8.plot: The quads want to sell a new shoe prototype that Tom invented, but they become convinced that someone is trying to steal his idea.

9.title: The Mighty Quad Squad
9.plot: The quads create superhero costumes for a child's birthday party; when a video of Nicky as Goggle Man goes viral, the popularity goes to his head.

10.title: Quaddy-Shack
10.plot: Ricky befriends a group of sophisticated country club children who challenge the quads to a high-stakes mini-golf match.

11.title: Go Hollywood, Part 1
11.plot: The quads win their family a vacation to Hollywood, and find themselves caught up in a case of mistaken identity.

12.title: Go Hollywood, Part 2
12.plot: The quads win their family a vacation to Hollywood, and find themselves caught up in a case of mistaken identity.

13.title: Rock 'n' Rules
13.plot: The quads decide to secretly rent out the garage in order to have money to make their own house rules.

14.title: Ballet and the Beasts
14.plot: Dawn joins a ballet class to have her own activity away from her brothers, but her plan is spoiled when the boys join the class too.

15.title: She Blinded Him with Science (Bob)
15.plot: Nicky, Dicky and Dawn challenge Ricky's firm disbelief in superstitions, but they go too far in proving him wrong.

16.title: Harpers for President
16.plot: Ricky is confident in his ability to get elected as class president until Dawn enters the race; Nicky and Dicky go from being Ricky and Dawn's running mates to their rivals.

17.title: Doggy Door Afternoon
17.plot: Squishy Paws runs away when the quads are home alone, and they argue about who should be in charge of the search.

18.title: Three Men and a Mae B
18.plot: Dawn must run a tricky game of interference when each of the boys reveals they have started to look at Mae in a different light.

19.title: Diary of an Angry Quad
19.plot: Dawn plans to get back at Nicky, Ricky and Dicky for reading her diary one too many times, leading none of them to trust each other.

20.title: Quad Court
20.plot: The quads create a courtroom in their garage to settle their own arguments and end up using the court to pass judgment on friends and classmates.

21.title: The Quad-Plex
21.plot: The siblings try to avoid being seen at the movies with their parents for fear of looking ''uncool.''

22.title: Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Sicky
22.plot: When Dawn gets sick Nicky, Ricky and Dicky must survive the day without her but they fall apart.

23.title: Mission: Un-Quaddable
23.plot: The quads are excited when action star JT Steele comes to live with them while researching his latest role.

24.title: A Brief Case of Popularity
24.plot: While trying to fit in with the coolest people in school, Nicky, Dicky and Dawn must keep Ricky from making them look uncool.

25.title: New Kid on the Block
25.plot: The quads try to make friends with their new neighbor in order to get access to her cool tree house, but soon discover that she is not what she seems.

26.title: The Tell-Tale Art
26.plot: Dawn grows suspicious of her brothers when Ricky takes credit for artwork that Dicky painted and Ricky uses Dicky's ideas for his own gain.

1.title: Quad with a Blog
1.plot: The quads try to save Get Sporty's Café after a food blogger's rave review of a neighboring cafe puts theirs in jeopardy.

2.title: Odd Quad Out
2.plot: Nicky, Ricky, Dicky and Dawn are tired of being lumped together as ''the quads'' until another set of quadruplets steals the spotlight from them.

3.title: Keeping Up with the Quadashians
3.plot: After binge watching their favorite reality TV show, the quads decide to make a show of their own.

4.title: The Great Mullet Caper
4.plot: The quads are judgmental about Tom and Anne's plans for the new cafe, but a wild adventure teaches them not to be so quick to judge.

5.title: Quadsled
5.plot: The quads get on each other's nerves so much that they have trouble sleeping on the night before an important bobsled race.

6.title: Ye Olde Hand Holde
6.plot: When Dawn boasts that she is more mature than the boys and is ready to go on a first date, a competition is sparked between the quads.

7.title: What's the Worst That Quad Happen?
7.plot: The quads must try to behave for two days and resist opening a mysterious present, but quickly find out how badly things can go if they do not follow the rules.

8.title: To Be Invited or Not to Be
8.plot: The quads make a new friend, an amazing inventor, but when not all of them get invited back to hang out again, they start to wonder why.

9.title: Ele-Funk in the Room
9.plot: When Dawn and Mae have a falling out, Dawn forbids Nicky, Ricky and Dicky from going to an upcoming concert with her, but the boys have other plans in mind.

10.title: Tween Wolf
10.plot: The Quads' eavesdropping threatens to ruin their annual boys vs. girls scare night camp out because of a misunderstanding about going through the change.

11.title: This Little Piggy Went to the Harpers
11.plot: When The Quads kidnap a rival soccer team's pig mascot as a prank, they have to pass it off as Anne's surprise birthday present to avoid being caught forgetting her birthday.

12.title: I Want My Mae B. Back
12.plot: Dawn becomes jealous when Mae starts spending time with Miles, so she enlists the help of her brothers to separate them.

13.title: The Buffa-Lowdown
13.plot: When Ricky is put in charge of school news production, he lets the power go into his head. However, when the rest of the Harper quadruplets realize why he's doing it, they come together to help him.

14.title: The Quadshank Redemption
14.plot: The Harper quads get detention, forcing them to miss the school carnival and the only way for them to make it to the carnival before it ends, is if they work with some of the bad kids.

15.title: Not-So-Sweet Charity
15.plot: When the boys put on a talent show for charity to impress some girls, Dawn's secret almost gets revealed.

16.title: One Quadzy Summer
16.plot: The boys try to ruin Dawn and Mae's perfect summer after the girls get summer jobs at the Boulderly Hills Country Club.

17.title: Quad for Teacher
17.plot: The Quads accidentally force out the easygoing gym teacher, ruining the class for everyone; they think they've fixed everything with the perfect substitutes, but soon realize their parents have made things worse.

18.title: Quadpendence Day
18.plot: The Harper quads declare their own independence when Dawn decides to get her ears pierced and her brothers decide to get a snake as a pet without asking for permission from their parents.

19.title: Cementing the Quads' Legacy
19.plot: The quads want to pull off a big stunt so that their class will be remembered by future students, but when they find out that the personal legacy they are leaving behind is not great, they have to fix both before it is too late.

20.title: #QUADGOALS
20.plot: The quads try to take the perfect picture at their Aunt Jackie's farm to best their rival quadruplets, the Kramdens, but end up hurting their aunt's chances to win a contest in the process.

21.title: A Space Quadyssey
21.plot: Ricky is accepted into a junior astronaut training program, but only if his siblings join him.

22.title: Yoco
22.plot: The Harpers get a new gadget that runs their entire household, but the quads take things a little too far when they are left alone with it.

23.title: The Wonderful Wizard of Quads: Part 1
23.plot: When a famous theater director comes to town for auditions of The Wizard Of Oz, the quads know they were born to play these parts. But when Dawn doesn't get the part of Dorothy right away, she's on a mission to prove she is way better at acting then a diva theater star.

24.title: The Wonderful Wizard of Quads: Part 2
24.plot: When Dawn does not get the part of Dorothy in The Wizard of Oz, she goes on a mission to prove she deserves the role.

locations: Stage 19, Paramount Studios - 5555 Melrose Avenue, Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA
